  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer (ACMV)",
  "description": "<p><strong>JOB RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p><ul><li>Project coordination and supervision of site M&E service include installation, testing & commissioning</li><li>Determine project specifications by studying product design, customer requirements, and performance standards, completing technical studies, and preparing cost estimates</li><li>Liaise & work closely with clients, main contractors on the progress of works</li><li>Prepare construction drawings, specifications, shop drawings, method statements & local codes and regulations</li><li>Schedule & monitor work program and activities to ensure target completion dates of works are met</li><li>Liaise with supplier/ vendors/ subcontractors to ensure on-time delivery of materials</li><li>Ensure a safe environment on-site or maintain all quality and safety records</li><li>Supervise all works performed by subcontractors at the site to ensure that quality works are produced and meet client's requirement</li><li>Be familiar with BIM, REVIT MEP, NAVIS Works, Autocad</li><li>Able to do static calculation for ACMV system</li><li>Other duties as assigned</li></ul><p><strong>Job requirements</strong></p><ul><li>A least Diploma or above in Mechanical/Building Engineering or equivalent </li><li>At least 3 Year(s) of working experience in ACMV is preferred </li></ul>",
